.TH "set_swbp" 9 "set_swbp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
set_swbp \- store breakpoint at a given address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" set_swbp
.BI "(struct arch_uprobe *auprobe "  ","
.BI "struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long vaddr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "auprobe" 12
arch specific probepoint information.
.IP "mm" 12
the probed process address space.
.IP "vaddr" 12
the virtual address to insert the opcode.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For mm \fImm\fP, store the breakpoint instruction at \fIvaddr\fP.
Return 0 (success) or a negative errno.
